                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nCarbon monoxide poisoning results in the displacement of oxygen from hemoglobin in the blood, resulting in tissue hypoxia. Although options 1, 2 and 4 are appropriate interventions in the care of a client with carbon monoxide poisoning, the first action the nurse would take to assist the client’s airway and breathing would be to apply high-flow oxygen via a nonrebreather mask. Therefore, option 3 is correct.",
